  "text": "## LLVM Pass Manager Registration and Execution Chain\n\n### Overview\nLLVM's optimization pass system uses a sophisticated chain of components to register, manage, and execute transformation passes. This trace covers both the legacy pass manager and the new pass manager (NPM) infrastructure.\n\n### 1. Pass Manager Template (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h)\nThe core PassManager is a template class that manages a sequence of passes over a particular unit of IR (Module, Function, Loop, etc.). Key aspects:\n- **Template Definition** (lines 159-226): `template <typename IRUnitT, typename AnalysisManagerT = AnalysisManager<IRUnitT>, typename... ExtraArgTs> class PassManager`\n- **addPass() Method** (lines 193-214): Adds passes to the manager using concept-based polymorphism, storing them in a vector of unique_ptr<PassConceptT>\n- **run() Method** (lines 188-191): Declared here, implemented in PassManagerImpl.h\n- **Type Aliases**: ModulePassManager (line 238), FunctionPassManager (line 247)\n\n### 2. PassRegistry (llvm/include/llvm/PassRegistry.h)\nManages the registration and initialization of the pass subsystem. Key components:\n- **getPassRegistry()** (line 58): Returns the global registry object initialized at application startup\n- **registerPass()** (line 70): Registers a pass (by PassInfo) with the registry, required for use with PassManager\n- **getPassInfo()** (lines 62, 66): Looks up a pass's PassInfo by type identifier or argument string\n- **PassInfoMap** (line 43): DenseMap storing PassInfo objects indexed by pass type pointer\n- **PassInfoStringMap** (line 45): StringMap for lookup by command-line argument\n\n### 3. Pass Registration Macros (llvm/include/llvm/PassSupport.h)\nThe registration system uses macros to automate pass setup:\n- **INITIALIZE_PASS_BEGIN/END** (lines 39-54): Macro pair that creates initialization functions and PassInfo objects\n  - Creates `initialize<PassName>PassOnce()` function containing registration code\n  - Defines `PassInfo` with pass name, argument, ID, constructor function, and analysis flags\n  - Calls `Registry.registerPass(*PI, true)` to register the pass\n  - Uses `llvm::once_flag` for thread-safe initialization (lines 50-54)\n- **INITIALIZE_PASS_DEPENDENCY** (line 42): Declares pass dependencies during initialization\n- **RegisterPass Template** (lines 89-98): Alternative registration mechanism for simple cases\n  - Inherits from PassInfo\n  - Calls `PassRegistry::getPassRegistry()->registerPass(*this)` in constructor\n\nExample from llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp (lines 6331-6343):\n```cpp\nINITIALIZE_PASS_BEGIN(InstructionCombiningPass, \"instcombine\",\n                      \"Combine redundant instructions\", false, false)\nINITIALIZE_PASS_DEPENDENCY(AssumptionCacheTracker)\nINITIALIZE_PASS_DEPENDENCY(TargetLibraryInfoWrapperPass)\nINITIALIZE_PASS_END(InstructionCombiningPass, \"instcombine\",\n                    \"Combine redundant instructions\", false, false)\n```\n\n### 4. PassInfo Class (llvm/include/llvm/PassInfo.h)\nStores metadata about a pass:\n- **PassName** (line 34): Human-readable name\n- **PassArgument** (line 35): Command-line argument to enable the pass\n- **PassID** (line 36): Type identifier (pointer to static char)\n- **NormalCtor_t** (line 39): Function pointer to create pass instances\n- **createPass()** (lines 84-88): Creates an instance of the pass\n\n### 5. Pass Manager Execution (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerImpl.h)\nThe run() method implements the actual pass execution chain (lines 27-98):\n\n**Execution Flow**:\n1. Gets PassInstrumentation from the analysis manager (lines 62-64)\n2. Iterates over each pass in the Passes vector (line 67)\n3. For each pass:\n   - Calls `PI.runBeforePass()` instrumentation callbacks (lines 73-74)\n   - Executes the pass: `PassPA = Pass->run(IR, AM, ExtraArgs...)` (line 76)\n   - Invalidates analyses based on PreservedAnalyses result: `AM.invalidate(IR, PassPA)` (line 80)\n   - Calls `PI.runAfterPass()` instrumentation callbacks (line 84)\n   - Intersects preserved analysis sets (line 88)\n4. Returns aggregated PreservedAnalyses (line 97)\n\n### 6. Pass Pipeline Building (llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h & llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp)\n\n**PassBuilder Class** manages construction of standard pipelines:\n- **registerModuleAnalyses()** (line 157): Populates ModuleAnalysisManager with all available module analyses\n- **registerFunctionAnalyses()** (line 173): Populates FunctionAnalysisManager\n- **registerLoopAnalyses()** (line 180): Populates LoopAnalysisManager\n- **buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()** (line 249): Constructs the core module optimization pipeline\n- **buildFunctionSimplificationPipeline()** (line 205): Constructs function-level simplification pipeline\n- **buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline()** (line 258): Builds default O1/O2/O3 per-module pipeline\n\n**buildModuleOptimizationPipeline Implementation** (PassBuilderPipelines.cpp, lines 1477-1600+):\nFor O2/O3, the module optimization pipeline adds passes in this order:\n1. PartialInlinerPass() (line 1486) - optional partial inlining\n2. EliminateAvailableExternallyPass() (line 1498) - removes external definitions\n3. ReversePostOrderFunctionAttrsPass() (line 1503) - propagates function attributes\n4. PGO instrumentation passes (lines 1510-1517)\n5. RecomputeGlobalsAAPass() (line 1528) - alias analysis\n6. invokeOptimizerEarlyEPCallbacks() (line 1530) - extension point for custom passes\n7. Function optimization passes wrapped with adaptor:\n   - DropUnnecessaryAssumesPass() (line 1538)\n   - LoopVersioningLICMPass() + LICMPass() (lines 1546-1552)\n   - Float2IntPass(), LowerConstantIntrinsicsPass() (lines 1555-1556)\n   - ControlHeightReductionPass() (line 1566) - O3 only\n   - Loop passes: LoopRotatePass(), LoopDeletionPass(), LoopInterchangePass() (lines 1580-1590)\n   - LoopVectorization (line 1575)\n   - SLPVectorizer (implied in vectorizer callbacks)\n\n**buildFunctionSimplificationPipeline Implementation** (PassBuilderPipelines.cpp, lines 591-750+):\nCore function-level optimizations executed in O1/O2/O3:\n1. CountVisitsPass() (line 604)\n2. SROAPass() (line 608) - scalar replacement of aggregates\n3. EarlyCSEPass() (line 611) - early common subexpression elimination\n4. AssumeSimplifyPass() (line 613)\n5. GVNHoistPass(), GVNSinkPass() (lines 617-623) - global value numbering\n6. SpeculativeExecutionPass() (line 627)\n7. JumpThreadingPass(), CorrelatedValuePropagationPass() (lines 630-631)\n8. SimplifyCFGPass(), InstCombinePass(), AggressiveInstCombinePass() (lines 640-642) - **Key simplification passes**\n9. LibCallsShrinkWrapPass() (line 645)\n10. TailCallElimPass() (line 655)\n11. ReassociatePass() (line 663)\n12. Loop passes (LPM1, LPM2) with function adaptor (lines 677-742):\n    - LoopInstSimplifyPass(), LoopSimplifyCFGPass()\n    - LICMPass() (loop invariant code motion)\n    - LoopRotatePass()\n    - SimpleLoopUnswitchPass()\n    - LoopIdiomRecognizePass(), IndVarSimplifyPass()\n    - LoopDeletionPass()\n    - LoopFullUnrollPass()\n13. VectorCombinePass() (line 749)\n\n### 7. Pass Registry Definition (llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def)\nDefines all available passes with MODULE_PASS, FUNCTION_PASS, CGSCC_PASS, LOOP_PASS, and MODULE_ANALYSIS macros.\n\nExample entries (lines 54-120):\n- `MODULE_PASS(\"always-inline\", AlwaysInlinerPass())`\n- `MODULE_PASS(\"attributor\", AttributorPass())`\n- `MODULE_PASS(\"globalopt\", GlobalOptPass())`\n- `MODULE_PASS(\"inliner-wrapper\", ModuleInlinerWrapperPass())`\n\nThese are expanded in PassBuilder.cpp to create parser hooks.\n\n### 8. Pass Initialization (llvm/include/llvm/InitializePasses.h)\nDeclares initialization functions for each pass library:\n- `initializeCore()` - Core passes\n- `initializeTransformUtils()` - Transform utilities\n- `initializeScalarOpts()` - Scalar optimizations\n- `initializeVectorization()` - Vectorization passes\n- `initializeInstCombine()` - InstCombine pass\n- `initializeIPO()` - Inter-procedural optimizations\n- Individual pass initialization functions like `initializeInstructionCombiningPassPass()`\n\n### Key Execution Chain\n\n1. **Registration Phase** (at startup):\n   - `initializeCore()` and related functions call per-pass `initialize<PassName>Pass(PassRegistry&)`\n   - INITIALIZE_PASS_END macro creates PassInfo and calls `Registry.registerPass()`\n   - PassRegistry stores all PassInfo objects in PassInfoMap\n\n2. **Pipeline Construction** (when building optimization pipeline):\n   - `PassBuilder::buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline()` or similar is called\n   - This calls `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()` and `buildFunctionSimplificationPipeline()`\n   - These methods call `ModulePassManager::addPass()` for each optimization pass\n   - `addPass()` wraps the pass in a PassModel concept object and stores in vector\n\n3. **Execution Phase** (when running pipeline):\n   - `ModulePassManager::run(Module&, ModuleAnalysisManager&)` is called\n   - PassManager iterates through Passes vector\n   - For each pass, calls `Pass->run(IR, AM, ExtraArgs...)`\n   - After each pass, `AnalysisManager::invalidate()` updates cached analysis results\n   - Returns aggregated PreservedAnalyses\n\n### Summary\nLLVM's pass system is built on:\n- **Static registration** via INITIALIZE_PASS macros and PassRegistry for pass metadata\n- **Template-based PassManager** for type-safe pass execution\n- **Concept-based polymorphism** in PassManagerImpl for dynamic dispatch\n- **Pipeline builders** that construct O2/O3 pipelines with specific pass ordering\n- **Analysis management** that caches and invalidates results between passes\n- **Extension points** (EPCallbacks) allowing custom passes to be inserted\n"
